Taiwan Stocks: Chang Hwa Commercial, First Financial, Wintek

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-22T06:12:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/taiwan-stocks-chang-hwa-commercial-first-financial-wintek.html
Stocks of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index rose 40.33, or 0.5 percent, to 8,508.04.  Financials:  Chang Hwa Commercial Bank (2801)  (2801 TT) surged 6
percent to NT$22.85, the most since Dec. 29.  Taiwan Business
Bank (2834)  (2834 TT) gained 3.6 percent to NT$11.55. First Financial
Holding Co. (2892 TT) increased 2.3 percent to NT$24.60. Support
for consolidation in the financial industry continues under Yuh
Chang Chen, who became chairman of the commission last year,
Vice-Chairwoman Lee Jih-chu said by phone today, confirming an
earlier report by the Economic Daily News. The government
doesn’t have a preference for any particular companies to merge,
she said.  Wintek Corp. (2384)  (2384 TT) advanced 1.7 percent to NT$53.30.
The display supplier’s board approved plans to invest an
additional $120 million in two liquid-crystal display factories
in Dongguan,  China , the Taichung, Taiwan-based company said in
two exchange statements yesterday. The panel maker also plans to
pay a cash dividend of NT$1.03 per share of its 2010 earnings,
according to a separate exchange statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
